===Etymology===
A late formation ({{zh-m|*後起字}}). Earlier forms of southern Chinese toponyms using the character were often written with the homophone {{ltc-l|步}} in historical records dated from the {{w|Northern Wei}} to {{w|Ming dynasty|Ming}} dynasties, which has been conjectured to be a transcription of an earlier {{bor|zh|qfa-tak|-}} word ({{zh-ref|Kang, 2010}}). Cf. {{zh-m|墟|gloss=market}}.

